  "time_ut": 1662378977,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0db4\u0ddc\u0dbd\u0dca \u0db8\u0dab\u0dca\u0da9\u0dbd\u0dba\u0dda \u0d85\u0dbb\u0dca\u0dae \u0dc3\u0dcf\u0db0\u0d9a\u0dba\u0da7 \u0dc0\u0dd2\u0daf\u0dca\u0daf \u0d9a\u0dbd\u0db8\u0db1\u0dcf\u0d9a\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0dba,\u0dc3\u0dd0\u0db8\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dcf \u0dba\u0dc5\u0dd2 \u0dbb\u0dd2\u0db8\u0dcf\u0db1\u0dca\u0da9\u0dca",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Scientific manager, husband remanded to Pol Board's meaning factor",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Kaduwela Magistrate Mrs. Chamini Wijebandara today (05) ordered that the subject clerk of the Coconut Cultivation Board and her husband be further remanded until the 19th, for allegedly embezzling more than seven and a half million rupees from the Employees Provident Fund of the Coconut Cultivation Board.",
        "The Magistrate issued this order after taking into consideration the facts submitted by the Criminal Investigation Department to the court that the investigation regarding the incident has not been completed.",
        "R., a resident of Monaragala Okkampitiya, who is the subject clerk of the Coconut Cultivation Board, was further remanded in custody. M. Tamara Dilhani and R. D. A couple named Upul Ratnayake.",
        "The Criminal Investigation Department submitted to the court that several suspects should be arrested and further statements should be recorded regarding this fraud.",
        "Mr. Rienzi Arsakularatne, who appeared on behalf of the suspects, stated that since his client's youngest child is three months old, he should be granted bail on any condition.",
        "Advocate Mr. Kamal Wijesiri, who appeared in court for the Coconut Cultivation Board, stated that since the suspects had committed this offense while the child was about to be delivered, they were aware of the offense and therefore objected to the granting of bail.",
        "Taking into account the facts presented, the court ordered the suspects to be further remanded until the 19th and adjourned the case to that day."
      ],
